                                  <locus from="76v" to="77r"/>
                                  <desc type="GuestText"><title ref="LIT7138PrLover">Prayer of the lover</title></desc>
                                  <note>
                                      Ethiopic prayer, entitled  <q xml:lang="grc">περη αγαπης κὲ εφτηχία</q>.
                                      It begins as follows: <q xml:lang="gez">
                                          በስመ፡ አብ፡ <gap reason="ellipsis" resp="bm:GrebTiss1935Codices"/> <sic>ጸሎተ፡</sic> <sic>ምስተ<surplus>፡</surplus>ፋቅር፨</sic> 
                                          አስማተ፡ ንዋይ፡ ምስሓበ፡ ንዋይ፨ አስተፋቅር፡ ወአስተዋድድ፡ ወአስተ<surplus>፡</surplus>ሳልም፨
                                      </q>, and concludes as follows: 
                                      <q xml:lang="gez">ኵሎሙ፡ ሰብአ፡ ሃገር፡ <sic>ወሉደ፡</sic> አዳም፡ ወሔዋን፡ ይሰግዱ፡ ለገብርከ፡ እገሌ፨
                                      </q>.
                                      The use of this formula is explained on <locus target="#77rb"/> in Greek and Gǝʿǝz-Amharic as follows: 
                                      <q xml:lang="grc">τά άνωθεν τά γράφης σε πετζή γενας μπράια μεγάλη</q>
                                      <q xml:lang="am">የላይኛውን፡ ቃል፡ በብርሃና፡ ጸሀፎ፡ <surplus resp="bm:GrebTiss1935Codices">ለ</surplus>ትጽህፎ፡ በወርቅ፡ ቀለም፡ 
                                          በሰባ<supplied reason="omitted">ዕ</supplied>ቱ፡ ቀለማት፡ ፪<del rend="expunctuated">ገ</del>ጊዜ፡</q>
                                  </note>
